—The ghosts of calamitous [text corrupt] and earthbound growths;
—The ghosts who sing alone, dance in solitude, or laugh without cause;
—The ghosts of sorcery, wild paths, and poisonous arts;
—The mountain spirits, cliff demons, and hundred *mei* specters;
—The Eight Divisions’ plague-bearing ghosts;
—The ghosts who call out to human souls;
—The ghosts with various names;
—The ghosts of *Minggong* and stone anchors;
—The nameless, unregistered ghosts;
—The ghosts of puppies beneath trees;
—The ghosts of night-wandering malevolence;
—The ghosts of mountain forests, earth altars, and perverse shrines;
—The ghosts of the Four Guardian Deities’ slain generals;
—The ghosts of blades, warfare, and headless, handless soldiers;
—The ghost of Wu King Zixu;
—The ghosts of the Red Eyebrows and bandits;
—The ghosts of the Three Kings, Five Hegemons, and defeated armies’ slain generals;
—The ghosts of dysentery and swelling;
—The ghosts of *Lǔ Dīng*’s jaundice, cramps, coughs, and vomiting;
—The ghost of *Lǐ Zǐ’áo* of the clouds, and the thousand spirits and ten thousand *mei*;
—The ghosts who shake bells, blow horns, and call out;
—The ghosts of hanging;
—The drowned ghosts;
—The ghosts of Qiang and Liao tribes;
—The ghosts of the Six Barbarians;
—The ghosts of Hu, Di, Man, and Rong tribes;
—The Green Affliction ghosts of the East;
—The Red Affliction ghosts of the South;
—The White Affliction ghosts of the West;
—The Black Affliction ghosts of the North;
—The Yellow Affliction ghosts of the Center;
—The ghosts of extinguished households;
—The ghosts of sudden, strange illnesses and deaths;
—The ghosts of white baldness and leprosy;
—The ghosts of festering sores and foul decay;
—The ghosts of market executions, beheadings, and hangings;
—The ghosts of crows and magpies’ chaotic, ominous cries;
—The ghosts of starvation, cold, and freezing deaths;
—The ghosts who conceal their forms and hide their shadows;
—The ghosts of reckless speech and false words;
—The ghosts of the Six Domestic Animals;
—The ghosts who suppress human souls;
—The ghosts of unburied white bones;
—The newly dead who shoot arrows to claim lives;
—The ghosts with rat heads and human bodies;
—The ghosts with ox heads and human bodies;
—The ghosts with tiger heads and human bodies;
—The ghosts with rabbit heads and human bodies;
—The ghosts with dragon heads and human bodies;
—The ghosts with snake heads and human bodies;
—The ghosts with horse heads and human bodies;
—The ghosts with sheep heads and human bodies;
—The ghosts with monkey heads and human bodies;
—The ghosts with dog heads and human bodies;
—The ghosts with pig heads and human bodies.

May all these be seized and bound. May the world know great peace, ghosts and spirits cease their rise, winds and rains harmonize, and the myriad people live in joy. Overwhelmed by such boundless grace, your disciple bows once more.

